attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[Μ(ᾶρκον)]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">Οὐαλέριον\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του\">Δι[ογνή-]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[το]υ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μηγαν\">Μηγαν\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"υἱὸν\">υἱὸν\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">[Χόρ-]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[τ]ωνα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">εὐεργέταν\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΕΣΛΙΛΥΒΑ[....]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[..]\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του\">ΔΙ[....]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[..]Υ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μηγαν\">ΜΗΓΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"υἱὸν\">ΥΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[.]ΩΝΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">ΕΥΕΡΓΕΤΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text following Kaibel's interpretation of Gualtherus' transcription\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΙΡΕΣΔΙΛΙΟΑbOI\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟ ΟΝΔΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΥΛΗΡΑΝΥΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΩΝΑΕΧΕΡΣΕΤΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The surviving manuscript tradition for this stone is extremely poor and confused. The transcription recorded by Tardia seems to conflate and repeat lines from the version of Gualtherus. The resolution proposed by Kaibel, of Gualtherus' text, as followed here, seems the least worst solution. A second, similar honorific for the same man is recorded in IG XIV.277 = CIL. X.7240 (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001097\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001097\u003C/a>, also lost and preserved in the antiquarian tradition). However, \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001660\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001660\u003C/a> = SEG 34.951 records honours for the father Diognetos Megas, providing some confirmation of the tradition, and confirming that Megas is a second name.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 234 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 128 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.18, no.21 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl.18, no.21 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5493 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">273\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Wilson 1990 317 n.15 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Gualtherus records lunate epsilon\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[240,243,246,249,252,255,258,261],{"id":241,"html":242},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ΕΣ Λιλυβα[ῖται] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[Μ(ᾶρκον)]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">Οὐαλέριον\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του\">Δι[ογνή-]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[το]υ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μηγαν\">Μηγαν\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"υἱὸν\">υἱὸν\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">[Χόρ-]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[τ]ωνα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">εὐεργέταν\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΕΣΛΙΛΥΒΑ[....]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[..]\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Οὐαλέριον\">ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Διογνή \n                   του\">ΔΙ[....]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[..]Υ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronymic\" data-text=\"Μηγαν\">ΜΗΓΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"υἱὸν\">ΥΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">[...]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[.]ΩΝΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">ΕΥΕΡΓΕΤΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":244,"html":245},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>",{"id":247,"html":248},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text following Kaibel's interpretation of Gualtherus' transcription\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΙΡΕΣΔΙΛΙΟΑbOI\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΟΥΑΛΕΡΙΟ ΟΝΔΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΥΛΗΡΑΝΥΙΟΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΩΝΑΕΧΕΡΣΕΤΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":250,"html":251},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":253,"html":254},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The surviving manuscript tradition for this stone is extremely poor and confused. The transcription recorded by Tardia seems to conflate and repeat lines from the version of Gualtherus. The resolution proposed by Kaibel, of Gualtherus' text, as followed here, seems the least worst solution. A second, similar honorific for the same man is recorded in IG XIV.277 = CIL. X.7240 (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001097\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001097\u003C/a>, also lost and preserved in the antiquarian tradition). However, \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001660\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001660\u003C/a> = SEG 34.951 records honours for the father Diognetos Megas, providing some confirmation of the tradition, and confirming that Megas is a second name.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":256,"html":257},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 234 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 128 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.18, no.21 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl.18, no.21 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5493 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">273\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Wilson 1990 317 n.15 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":259,"html":260},"handnote","\u003Cp>Gualtherus records lunate epsilon\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":262,"html":263},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[265,267,270,271],{"html":266},"Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares",{"id":268,"lang":102,"html":269},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ΕΣ Λιλυβα[ῖται] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον Οὐαλέριον Διογνή \n                   του Μηγαν υἱὸν Χόρ\n                   τωνα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Μᾶρκον\">[Μ(ᾶρκον)]\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" da